        "title": "Equation of the Tangent Line at a Given Point",
        "text": "For $$y$$ to be tangent to f, the slope of $$y$$ must be an instantaneous rate of change of some point on f. We need to take the derivative of f.",
        "variabilization": {},
        "oer": "",
        "license": ""
    },
    {
        "id": "a4a2093derivative29a-h2",
        "type": "hint",
        "dependencies": [
            "a4a2093derivative29a-h1"
        ],
        "title": "Definition of Derivative",
        "text": "lim h\u21920 $$\\frac{f{\\left(x+h\\right)}-f{\\left(x\\right)}}{h}$$",
        "variabilization": {},
        "oer": "",
        "license": ""
    },
    {
        "id": "a4a2093derivative29a-h3",
        "type": "hint",
        "dependencies": [
            "a4a2093derivative29a-h2"
        ],
        "title": "Substitute",
        "text": "lim h\u21920 $$\\frac{f{\\left(x+h\\right)}-f{\\left(x\\right)}}{h}$$ $$=$$ lim h\u21920 $$\\frac{\\left(x+h\\right)^2-k\\left(x+h\\right)-x^2-kx}{h}$$",
        "variabilization": {},
        "oer": "",
        "license": ""
    },
    {
        "id": "a4a2093derivative29a-h4",
        "type": "hint",
        "dependencies": [
            "a4a2093derivative29a-h3"
        ],
        "title": "Distribute",
        "text": "lim h\u21920 $$\\frac{\\left(x+h\\right)^2-k\\left(x+h\\right)-x^2-kx}{h}$$ $$=$$ lim h\u21920 $$\\frac{x^2+2xh+h^2-kx-kh-x^2+kx}{h}$$",
        "variabilization": {},
        "oer": "",
        "license": ""
    },
    {
        "id": "a4a2093derivative29a-h5",
        "type": "hint",
        "dependencies": [
            "a4a2093derivative29a-h4"
        ],
        "title": "Simplify",
        "text": "lim h\u21920 $$\\frac{x^2+2xh+h^2-kx-kh-x^2+kx}{h}$$ $$=$$ lim h\u21920 $$\\frac{2xh+h^2-kh}{h}$$ $$=$$ lim h\u21920 $$2x+h-k$$",
        "variabilization": {},
        "oer": "",
        "license": ""
    },
    {
        "id": "a4a2093derivative29a-h6",
        "type": "hint",
        "dependencies": [
            "a4a2093derivative29a-h5"
        ],
        "title": "Apply Limit",
        "text": "lim h\u21920 $$2x+h-k$$ $$=$$ $$2x+0-k$$ $$=$$ $$2x-k$$",
        "variabilization": {},
        "oer": "",
        "license": ""
    },
    {
        "id": "a4a2093derivative29a-h7",
        "type": "hint",
        "dependencies": [
            "a4a2093derivative29a-h6"
        ],
        "title": "Find $$x$$",
        "text": "The tangent line must give us the same output as f: when does $$x^2-kx=4x-9$$?",
        "variabilization": {},
        "oer": "",
        "license": ""
    },
    {
        "id": "a4a2093derivative29a-h8",
        "type": "hint",
        "dependencies": [
            "a4a2093derivative29a-h7"
        ],
        "title": "System of Equations",
        "text": "Solve the system: $$4=2x-k$$ and $$x^2-kx=4x-9$$.",
        "variabilization": {},
        "oer": "",
        "license": ""
    },
    {
        "id": "a4a2093derivative29a-h9",
        "type": "hint",
        "dependencies": [
            "a4a2093derivative29a-h8"
        ],
        "title": "Substitute",
        "text": "Substitute $$k=2x-4$$ in the second equation: $$x^2-\\left(2x-4\\right) x=$$ $$-x^2+4x$$",
        "variabilization": {},
        "oer": "",
        "license": ""
    },
    {
        "id": "a4a2093derivative29a-h10",
        "type": "hint",
        "dependencies": [
            "a4a2093derivative29a-h9"
        ],
        "title": "Solve",
        "text": "$$-x^2+4x=4x-9$$ becomes $$-x^2=-9$$, and $$x=3$$ or $$x=-3$$",
        "variabilization": {},
        "oer": "",
        "license": ""
    },
    {
        "id": "a4a2093derivative29a-h11",
        "type": "hint",
        "dependencies": [
            "a4a2093derivative29a-h10"
        ],
        "title": "Substitute",
        "text": "for $$x=3$$, $$k=2(3)-4=2$$ and for $$x=-3$$, $$k=2(-3)-4=-10$$",
        "variabilization": {},
        "oer": "",
        "license": ""
    }
